This paper deals with action recognition using spatio-temporal representations in frame sequences. This is a common problem in computer vision, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new network architecture that can be trained end-to-end, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of motion blocks, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the network, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
